  "prompt": "Why isn't the Moon spinning?",
  "response": "The Moon does actually spin on its axis, but it is tidally locked to Earth. This means that the Moon takes the same amount of time to complete one rotation on its axis as it does to complete one orbit around Earth. As a result, the same side of the Moon always faces our planet. This tidal locking is a result of gravitational forces between Earth and the Moon, which have caused the Moon's rotational period to slow down over time until it became synchronized with its orbital period.",
